nl_ps: No student used her workstation. ## Mary is a student.

nl_ps: Smith attended a meeting. ## She chaired it.
label: e

nl_ps: Smith delivered a report to ITEL. ## She also delivered them an invoice. ## And she delivered them a project proposal.
fol_ps: DeliveredReport(smith, itel) ## exists x.exists y. (Woman(x) & Delivered(x, y) & Invoice(y) & DeliveredInvoice(x, y)) ## exists x.exists y. (Woman(x) & Project(y) & DeliveredProposal(x, y) & ProjectManager(x, y))
nl_h: Smith delivered a report, an invoice and a project proposal to ITEL.
fol_h: exists x.exists y.exists z. (Smith(x) & Report(y) & Invoice(z) & ProjectProposal(y) & DeliveredTo(x, y, z, ITEL))
label: e

nl_ps: Smith took a machine on Tuesday, and Jones took a machine on Wednesday. ## They put them in the lobby.
fol_ps: exists x.exists y. (Smith(x) & Machine(y) & TookOnTuesday(x, y)) & (Jones(x) & Machine(y) & TookOnWednesday(x, y)) ## exists x.exists y. (They(x) & PutIn(x, y) & InLobby(y))
nl_h: Smith and Jones put two machines in the lobby.
fol_h: exists x.exists y. (Smith(x) & Jones(y) & (PutMachine(x, lobby) & PutMachine(y, lobby)))
label: e

nl_ps: Each department has a dedicated line. ## The sales department rents it from BT.
nl_h: The sales department rents a line from BT.
label: e

nl_ps: GFI owns several computers. ## ITEL maintains them.
fol_ps: exists x. (GFI(x) & OwnsComputers(x)) ## exists x. (ITEL(x) & Maintains(x))
nl_h: ITEL maintains all the computers that GFI owns.
fol_h: exists x.exists y. (ITEL(x) & GFI(y) & MaintainsComputers(x, y))
label: e

nl_ps: Every customer who owns a computer has a service contract for it. ## MFI is a customer that owns exactly one computer.
fol_ps: exists x. (Customer(x) & OwnsComputer(x) & HasServiceContract(x)) ## exists x. (MFI(x) & OwnsExactlyOneComputer(x))
nl_h: MFI has a service contract for all its computers.
label: e

nl_ps: Every customer who owns a computer has a service contract for it. ## MFI is a customer that owns several computers.
fol_ps: exists x. (Customer(x) & OwnsComputer(x) & HasServiceContract(x)) ## exists x. (MFI(x) & OwnsSeveralComputers(x))
nl_h: MFI has a service contract for all its computers.
label: e

nl_ps: Every executive who had a laptop computer brought it to take notes at the meeting. ## Smith is a executive who owns five different laptop computers.
fol_ps: exists x. (Executive(x) & HadLaptopComputer(x) & BroughtToTakeNotesAtMeeting(x)) ## Executive(smith) & OwnsLaptopComputers(smith, 5)
nl_h: Smith took five laptop computers to the meeting.
fol_h: exists x. (Smith(x) & Took(x, y) & LaptopComputer(y) & NumberOf(y, 5) & AtMeeting(y))
label: n

nl_ps: A company director awarded himself a large payrise.
nl_h: A company director has awarded and been awarded a payrise.

nl_h: John said Bill had been hurt.
